  "market_context": "Bearish top-down analysis on ES futures. Daily chart highlighted a volume imbalance as the higher-time-frame point of interest, with price rallying back up to that zone, setting up a multi-timeframe short opportunity by drilling down from daily to 5-minute.",
  "key_observation": "The daily volume imbalance acted as the HTF POI; the hourly delivered the stop raid and displacement, the 15-minute confirmed sell-side liquidity into equilibrium, and the 5-minute provided a precise order block + fair value gap entry in the discount of the displacement range.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On the daily chart, identify the volume imbalance as the higher-time-frame point of interest where price is reaching back into.",
    "Step 2: Drop to the 1-hour chart and locate the stop raid followed by a displacement move up; mark out that displacement leg with the Fibonacci to find equilibrium/OTE.",
    "Step 3: Note that price is now retracing back into the hourly equilibrium of that displacement leg.",
    "Step 4: Drop to the 15-minute chart, identify sell-side liquidity below, and watch for an aggressive sweep of sell-side into the POI followed by displacement back up.",
    "Step 5: Reject the 15-minute fair value gap because it sits in the premium of the range and does not meet criteria.",
    "Step 6: Drop to the 5-minute chart, remove premium-zone arrays, and identify the discount fair value gap plus order block as the refined entry POI.",
    "Step 7: Plan the trade: enter on the 5-minute order block, stop on the order block low, partial at initial morning highs, then let runners run.",
    "Step 8: Confirm playout — price respects the entry zone and displaces higher (toward the short target on the inverted display) confirming the setup."
  ],
  "outcome": "Setup played out as planned — entry was respected and price displaced toward the targeted liquidity; partials taken at morning highs with runners left to run.",
  "lessons": "A complete top-down workflow requires HTF POI, mid-TF displacement and equilibrium, and an LTF entry POI in discount. Filter out fair value gaps sitting in premium and only execute when the order block + FVG align in the discount of the displacement range.",
